definition: and/as well as/and so/but (not)/yet (not)/(indicates causal relation)/(indicates change of state)/(indicates contrast)

sentences.english: Their personality bearing and the nobility of the character compels obedience naturally.
sentences.chinese: 他们的气质举止和高尚的性格让人们自然而然地折服。

sentences.english: As psychologists we have to question the natural.
sentences.chinese: 心理学家要对自然而然的反应提出疑问。

sentences.english: It is a sort of natural canonization.
sentences.chinese: 死亡是一种自然而然的超凡人圣。

sentences.english: With the accumulation of cute characters, a natural increase in the game playability .
sentences.chinese: 随着可爱人物的聚集，自然而然增加游戏的可玩性。

sentences.english: So you know, it was a natural meeting of the minds, I guess.
sentences.chinese: 所以，我们相遇是自然而然地相互吸引。

sentences.english: We don't even think about it in fact, to experience the high and then the low and high and then low.
sentences.chinese: 事实上根本不去思考，自然而然地经历起起落落。

sentences.english: But people are rooting for a credible No. 2.
sentences.chinese: 但是人们自然而然地寻找可靠的市场老二。

sentences.english: Taurus rules your ninth house, which is naturally one of the luckiest areas of your sign's chart.
sentences.chinese: 金牛座掌管你的第九宫，即星盘上最自然而然的幸运。

sentences.english: One possibility is that genes for antibiotic-resistance circulate naturally in wild populations.
sentences.chinese: 有可能是抗药基因会自然而然在野生物种间循环。

sentences.english: Naturally, you want to do something.
sentences.chinese: 自然而然，你希望有所作为。

sentences.english: The behavior of buyers and sellers naturally drives markets toward their equilibrium.
sentences.chinese: 买者和卖者的行为会自然而然的使市场趋于均衡。

sentences.english: With commitment, research and patience, the means will come.
sentences.chinese: 只要有恒心，研究和耐心，你会自然而然找到途径。

sentences.english: The prime minister fixes me with a self-consciously stern gaze.
sentences.chinese: 前首相自然而然地用严厉的目光盯着我。

sentences.english: The more intelligent spectators conclude that most people naturally float.
sentences.chinese: 聪明的看客认为大多数人都能自然而然地浮起来。

sentences.english: And naturally these have been made attune to the American way of thinking.
sentences.chinese: 自然而然地，这些系统以美国式的思考定音调音。

sentences.english: But you don't become "beautiful" just by virtue of2 the aging process.
sentences.chinese: 但你不会因为年龄的增长就自然而然地变得“美丽”。

definition: logical/only to be expected/rational and clearly structured (of text)
as it should be by rights (idiom); proper and to be expected as a matter of course/inevitable and right
over time/as time passes/in the fullness of time
lit. where water flows, a canal is formed (idiom)/fig. when conditions are right, success will follow naturally
